In order for the radios on the Dell BT370 & BT410 cards to function, these two quirks need to be added to hci_usb.c. This, however, is only half of the solution. The cards will start-up in HID mode, and are expected to be changed to HCI mode by a user space utility. If you would like to test the functionality with the quirks for these cards, you will need to use this patch: (until it is accepted to bluez):
http://article.gmane.org/gmane.linux.bluez.devel/15605
